summary:
It is in my nature to be curious, hardworking, imaginative, analytical and proactive. I fully engage in what I decide to pursue with dedication, passion and respect. I might become a little bit too excited when it comes to the concept of creation. All activities related to the arts, to the discovery, to insights and understanding, to be close to people and grow together: that's what triggers my energy and enthusiasm. 

I long for working in an environment able to nurture both my abilities and my dreams, able to provide opportunity where there's motivation and potential. I hope to find a space in a place where people matter, where people are trained and listened in a collaborative atmosphere.

projects:
[{'title': 'MSc Thesis in Behavioral Economics', 'date': {'start': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}}, 'description': "Inspired by the work of economists Shiv, Carmon and Ariely (2005) I decided to base my thesis on customer irrationality. The aim of the thesis, that will be completed within June, is to investigate whether marketing actions (such as pricing, advertising or, in this specific case, branding manipulation) can influence not only consumer's expectations towards a marketed product, but most important the actual efficacy of the product, generating a so-called placebo effect.
Another answer I aim to address is whether a moderator such as time delay can diminish the magnitude of the effect.

On this purposes, during the following months, an experiment will be conducted, involving students from the University of Amsterdam. The experiment design will be a 2 x 2 and will require 4 different treatments. After all data will be collected, a quantitative analysis will follow.

*Shiv, B., Carmon, Z., & Ariely, D. (2005). Placebo effects of marketing actions: Consumers may get what they pay for. Journal of marketing Research, 42(4), 383-393.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Chiara', 'last_name': 'Mainardi', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Procurement Specialist'}]}]
